body_html:
You can look at this gist:

https://gist.github.com/wolffg/541c97a74dfc0d77c4b8fd2a946a5b41

which is referred to here:

https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/tensorflow-for-poets/#5

which shows using Python to classify with the output of tensorflow/examples/image_retraining/retrain.py. It uses hardcoded pathnames, but you can get the idea.

Does that help?
